column5: Hi to every one whos thinking about going fishing this morning on lake Simcoe . From what i can see out my office window this morning ... lol and thats not much , i'd say it looks like the perch fishing should be good for a change out there this morning  after this weeks bad weather .. I  head'en out to the shop and hook up the boat and get out there before the sun get's up , any body know where the jumbo's are at ??? i think they moved in the last five days cause there not showing where they were .......
I have caught a few in Cook's Bay.  They have been deeper than usual.  Good luck.
Heading out Monday for some fun..  Hopefully some jumbos have moved into Kemp.
Heading out Monday too!  Hope to catch something!

i backed my boat in the water at Tiffen at 5 this morning and took it back out at 4:30 this after noon , What a day ,,,,, chassed all over the place looking for them jumbos , only caught a few the rest were a bit smaller , i started off in kempenfelt and ended up in Cooks Bay , burned thru 2 dozen worms , had a one hoursleep in theboat so i'd be ready for tthe three oclock feed but they wer'nt bitting , and yes thte only place to find them was in 50 feet of water today ................................

You'll be in luck , they have been there for the past two weeks , today they were hard to find , caught all mine in 50 feet of water , but still not the quota tho for spending  almost 12 hours on the water today .... Good luck ...................
